Navigating Career Path in Clinical Bioinformatics

To Become a Clinical Bioinformatician 

Career Interest: Connecting genetic information to health issues and to bridge research skills with practical applications for accurate and regulated patient diagnostics

Long Term goal: To contribute to the implementation of predictive models for disease risk individuals and appropriate reuse of clinical data for research purposes 

Education Plan: B.Sc in Biomedical Sciences. M.Sc in Clinical Informatics, Professional Certificates to demonstrate expertise.

Skill Development: Proficient inPython, Next-Generation Sequencing,R programming 

Networking: Participate in Bioinformatics related conferences like International Conference on Advanced Bioinformatics and Computational Biology, also connect with professionals.
